\section{Origin of the Project}

The awareness of the necessity for a senior community center near Carnegie Mellon University Campus emerged from my previous course project for Ecological Footprint in Fall 2013. In the analysis of the campus neighborhood, the conflict between  the relatively high ratio of senior population around campus and a lack of proper facilities for senior citizens was observed (\aref{AppendixA}).
\section{Proposed Site}
\subsection{Surrounding Buildings}
The proposed site of the senior center is to the north of the CMU campus next to Doherty Apartment across Forbes Ave. which is currently a parking lot (\fref{fig:siteLocation}). To the north of the proposed site is the East Campus Parking Garage. To the west of the site lie the alumni house and the Fraternity/Sorority Quadrangle. Doherty Appartment is to the east of the proposed site (\fref{fig:surroundingBd}).
