Average number of cars or other vehicles in the neighborhood is 1.8. The average estimated housing value (2010) for detached houses are \$516,844, which is four times that of the Pittsburgh average of \$132,337. The neighborhood is older than Pittsburgh average in terms of building built year. Most of the residents have a travel time of below 30 min. The majority of households in this are use gas to heat their house.The median rent is \$1,123, which is also a lot higher than \$603 of Pittsburgh in genera. This rent price is comparable to that of the renter occupied median housing cost in Stanford, which indicates the necessity to provide housing for the newly recruited faculty members (\tref{tab:midHousingcost}).
